title: PPPP’s Mumtaz Ali wins PS- 34 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP), Mumtaz Ali has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-34, Naushahro Feroze-3 by securing 52,385 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Shah Nazaw Jatoi of the Grand Democratic Alliance, who bagged votes 46,442.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 46.77 %.
